      "id": "2482614d_4db2827d",
      "file_path": "core/core-infrastructure/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/apex/core/infrastructure/threading/ThreadingTest.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 85,
      "message": "I'd prefer we switch back to await().  Can change \"atLeast\" to \"atMost\" and can change the time to \"2, SECONDS\" to give it plenty of time to get the thread running.  And of course, wait for all of the threads to start.\n\nA better approach, though, might be to modify ThreadingTestThread to take a CountDownLatch that's initialized to the number of threads and decremented by each thread at the appropriate point within its \"run\" method.  Then all we need on line 85 is to:\n\n  assertTrue(latch.await(2, SECONDS))",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
      "updated": "2020-06-11 16:42:36.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "42f7a442_140b2745",
      "unresolved": true
    },
